<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Avocado Dip</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Dips</cat>
        <cat>Ethnic</cat>
        <cat>Misc</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Avocado</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Crushed garlic clove</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Salt and pepper to taste</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Mayonnaise Lurie</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  mash the avocado, then blend in garlic, salt and pepper to taste. Then stir
  in mayo until the mixture is of the desired consistency. chill to serve.
  source My Aunt
  
